formed in poverty as de&s;tructive
to happine&s;s, prohibited his &s;uit.</P>
<P>Touched with chagrin and di&s;ap|pointment,
he immediately entered into
the &s;ervice of his Neapolitian maje&s;ty,
and &s;ought in the tumultuous &s;cenes of
