my drooping &s;pirits&mdash;to me the
effort of forgetfulne&s;s was ineffectual.
The loved idea of Angelo &s;till ro&s;e
upon my fancy, and its powers of cap|tivation,
heightened by ab&s;ence, and,
perhaps, even by de&s;pair, pur&s;ued me
with ince&s;&s;ant grief. I concealed in
<PB N="34" REF="38">
<GAP DESC="duplicate" EXTENT="1 page">
<PB N="35" REF="39">
<GAP DESC="duplicate" EXTENT="1 page">
<PB N="36" REF="40">
&s;ilence the angui&s;h that preyed upon
my heart, and re&s;igned my&s;elf a willing
victim to mona&s;tic au&s;terity. But I was
