&s;oul departed in a &s;hort deep &s;igh.</P>
<P>Her lover &s;inking back, endeavoured
to conceal his emotions, but the deep
&s;obs which agitated his brea&s;t, betrayed
his angui&s;h, and the tears of every &s;pec|tator
bedewed the &s;acred &s;pot where
beauty, &s;en&s;e, and innocence expired.</P>
<P>The organ now &s;welled in mournful
harmony; and the voices of the a&s;&s;embly
