of her friends into &s;ecurity.
It was otherwi&s;e with her&s;elf; &s;he was con&s;ci|ous
of the change, but forbore to afflict
them with the knowledge of the truth.
The hour of her di&s;&s;olution was &s;udden,
even to her&s;elf; but it was compo&s;ed,
and even happy. In the death of Cor|nelia
