he reached the bottom in &s;afety.</P>
<P>He now for the fir&s;t time &s;topped to
li&s;ten&mdash;the &s;ounds of pur&s;uit were cea&s;|ed,
and all was &s;ilent! Continuing to
wander on in ineffectual endeavours to
e&s;cape, his hands at length touched cold
iron, and he quickly perceived it be|longed
to a door. The door however
was fa&s;tened, and re&s;i&s;ted all his efforts
