<PB N="137" REF="141">
from his view. His heart thrilled with
&s;ecret agony, yet he re&s;olved to with|hold
his terrible conjectures from Julia,
of whom he learned that Ferdinand,
with her&s;elf, had been taken by banditti
in the way from the villa which had
offered them &s;o ho&s;pitable a reception
after the &s;hip-wreck. They were on
the road to a port whence they de&s;igned
again to embark for Italy, when this
misfortune overtook them. Julia add|ed
