<P>They had not been long in this &s;itua|tion,
when they heard a noi&s;e which
approached gradually, and which did
not appear to come from the avenue
they had pa&s;&s;ed.</P>
<P>The noi&s;e increa&s;ed, and they could
di&s;tingui&s;h voices. Hippolitus believed
the murderers were returned; that they
