and Hippolitus, de&s;cending from the
grate, became in&s;en&s;ible of his own
danger in his apprehen&s;ion for her.</P>
<P>In a &s;hort time all without was confu|&s;ion
<PB N="143" REF="147">
and uproar; the ruffian who had
