of this haunt of villainy from the
&s;on of a Sicilian nobleman, who had
fallen into the hands of this banditti,
and had afterwards e&s;caped from their
power.</P>
<P>The officers came attended by a
guard, and were every way prepared to
pro&s;ecute a &s;trenuous &s;earch through
