<P>The door was fa&s;tened by &s;trong iron
bolts, which Hippolitus vainly endea|voured
to draw. The voices drew near.
After much labour and difficulty the bolts
yielded&mdash;the door unclo&s;ed&mdash;and light
dawned upon them through the mouth
