<HEAD>CHAPTER XIV.</HEAD>
<P>WHEN Julia had re&s;ted, they fol|lowed
the track before them,
and in a &s;hort time arrived at a village
where they obtained &s;ecurity and re|fre&s;hment.</P>
<P>But Julia, who&s;e mind was occupied
